---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="The story behind Stackbase and why I build directories.">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-white mb-6">About</h1>
      
      <p class="text-xl text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed">
        I'm a solo builder who believes directories are underrated. In a world of algorithmic feeds, there's something powerful about well-organized, human-curated collections.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Story -->
  <section class="py-16 border-t border-zinc-800/50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-zinc max-w-none">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Why Directories?</h2>
        
        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
          I've spent years working on various web projects—SaaS apps, content sites, e-commerce stores. But I keep coming back to directories. There's something satisfying about organizing information in a way that helps people find exactly what they're looking for.
        </p>

        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
          A good directory isn't just a list of links. It's a curated experience. It understands user intent. It surfaces the right information at the right time. And when done well, it becomes the default resource for an entire niche.
        </p>

        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-8">
          That's what I'm building. Not just websites, but destination resources that people actually want to use.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">My Philosophy</h2>

        <div class="space-y-6 mb-8">
          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-zinc-800 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-1">Quality over Quantity</h3>
              <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">I don't take on every project. I focus on niches I understand and clients I can genuinely help. Two great directories beat ten mediocre ones.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-zinc-800 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-1">Performance First</h3>
              <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Slow sites don't rank. I use modern tools like Astro and Next.js to build directories that load instantly and score 95+ on Core Web Vitals.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-zinc-800 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M21 21l-6-6m2-5a7 7 0 11-14 0 7 7 0 0114 0z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-1">SEO is Strategy</h3>
              <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">I don't just build pretty sites—I build sites that rank. URL structure, internal linking, schema markup, and page speed are baked into every project from day one.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex gap-4">
            <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-zinc-800 flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 text-zinc-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 3a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0zM7 10a2 2 0 11-4 0 2 2 0 014 0z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-white mb-1">Honest Partnership</h3>
              <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">I won't promise you #1 rankings or instant traffic. What I will promise is solid work, transparent communication, and a site built on best practices that has the best chance to succeed long-term.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">What Makes Me Different</h2>
        
        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
          I'm not an agency. There's no account manager, no junior developer, no offshore team. When you work with me, you work with me. I handle everything from the initial conversation to the final deployment.
        </p>

        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-8">
          That means faster decisions, clearer communication, and a site that's actually built by the person you're talking to. It also means I can only take on a few projects at a time—which is exactly how I want it.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">My Work</h2>
        
        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-6">
          I currently run two directories:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3 mb-8">
          <li>
            <a href="https://indoorclimbinggym.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">IndoorClimbingGym.com</a>
            <span class="text-zinc-500"> — The largest directory of indoor climbing gyms worldwide. 7.5K URLs, 4.1K organic keywords, 463K impressions.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://golfsimmap.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300 transition-colors">GolfSimMap.com</a>
            <span class="text-zinc-500"> — Find golf simulators near you. Recently launched, hit DR 13 within a week.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="text-zinc-400 mb-8">
          These aren't case studies from years ago—they're live, growing projects that I actively maintain and improve.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-white mb-4">Let's Talk</h2>
        
        <p class="text-zinc-400">
          If you have a niche in mind—whether it's a hobby, an industry, or a local market—I'd love to hear about it. Not every niche is right for a directory, and I'll tell you honestly if I think yours has potential or not.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center mt-12">
        <a href="/pricing" class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 text-base font-medium text-zinc-950 bg-white rounded-lg hover:bg-zinc-200 transition-colors">
          View Pricing
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
